Task-Per-Derivative: 1
Task-Section: user
Task-Description: Tanglu with Fvwm-Nightshade desktop
Task-Extended-Description: Tanglu using the Fvwm-Nightshade Desktop
Task-Key: tanglu-fvwm-nightshade
Task-Seeds: desktop-common

= Hardware and Architecture Support =

== Architecture-independent ==

Bluetooth:

 * (blueman)

= Network Services =

Basic network services and Windows integration.

 * (avahi-autoipd)                  # IPv4 link-local interface configuration support
 * (network-manager-gnome)
 * (network-manager-pptp)
 * (network-manager-pptp-gnome)
 * (modemmanager)                   # Add support for mobile modem
 * (usb-modeswitch)
 * (mobile-broadband-provider-info)

= GUI infrastructure =
 * fvwm                             # Window manager
 * fvwm-nightshade                  # FVWM configuration - package currently not in Tanglu
 * stalonetray                      # Systray
 * xterm                            # Provide a backup terminal and complete X env.
 * xscreensaver                     # Locking and screen saving
 * librsvg2                         # SVG support
 * x11-apps                         # xwd, transset, ...
 * gksu                             # Graphical superuser access
 * (cpufrequtils)                   # control cpu states
 * (fdpowermon)                     # Battery status in systray
 * (pm-utils)                       # Suspend/hibernate support
 * (volumeicon)                     # Volume control in systray
 * (parcellite)                     # clipboard for systray


Extra fonts:
 * fonts-liberation
 * fonts-dejavu


Input methods:
 * (im-config)                      # For changing input method

= Desktop Fvwm-Nightshade Apps =
Rather than using the meta-packages they are deliberately expanded so
that we can select things a bit better.

Base:
 * python2.7
 * lightdm                          # Login manager
 * conky                            # For clock and cpu applets
 * feh                              # Wallpaper support
 * lxappearance                     # Gtk2/3 theme chooser
 * qt4-qtconfig                     # Qt4 theme chooser
 * pcmanfm                          # File manager with mount support
 * xarchiver                        # Frontend for archive tools
 * lxinput                          # Mouse-/keyboard config tool
 * (gpointing-device-settings)      # touchpad config
 * system-config-printer            # Printer manager
 * gnome-system-tools               # users-admin
 * gvfs-fuse                        # for access of non gio applications to gvfs mounts
 * gvfs-backends                    # for adding support for backends (photos, network etc ...) to gvfs
 * (ntp)                            # Add support for synchronisation with time servers
 * (font-manager)                   # Font configurator
 * (lxterminal)                     # 2nd terminal to xterm
 * (synaptic)                       # For our purposes, it's plumbing ...
 * (update-notifier)                # For crash report and updates notifications

User:
 * xfe                              # Filemanager with text editor (Xfw), text viewer, image viewer (Xfi)
 * (firefox)                        # Web browser
 * (icedove)                        # Email client
 * (pidgin)                         # Instant messaging client
 * (gimp)                           # Image Manipulation
 * (gmusicbrowser)                  # Music player
 * (mplayer2)                       # Video player
 * (xchm)                           # CHM viewer
 * galculator                       # calculator
 * (filezilla)                      # FTP/FTPS/SFTP client
 * (gufw)                           # Firewall
 * (xfburn)                         # CD/DVD burn program
 * (gmrun)                          # Comfortable launcher
 * (gpa)                            # GNU Privacy Assistant - only in Aequorea available
 * (hardinfo)                       # Displays system information
 * (guvcview)                       # UVC Viewer


Games: We only ship a few by default.
 * (ace-of-penguins)                # A set of games like under win :P

Themes: we will ship only the very best looking themes ;-)
These packages are included for size guidance until we have Tanglu-specific packages.

 * dmz-cursor-theme
 * gnome-themes-standard
 * (tanglu-theme-gnome)
 * (xcursor-themes)

Accessibility tools:
 * (xneurs)                         # Keyboard settings
 * (brltty)                         # Braille support

= Development =
Here we provide a minimal development environment sufficient to build kernel
drivers, so that this is possible on the live CD and in scenarios where
it is problematic to get these packages onto the installed system in order
to compile a driver. -mdz

 * (gcc)
 * (make)
